Follow the axillary nerve around the posterior aspect of the surgical neck of the humerus; its target is the deltoid muscle, the primary abductor of the glenohumeral joint. 
Follow the radial nerve to the posterior aspect of the humerus. It innervates, with no exception, the muscles of the posterior compartments of the arm and forearm.
